<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-03-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-03-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="734" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                            <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Bigelow</persName></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 411.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-03-05"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 5, 1866.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 15th ultimo, No.
                                273, together with its accompaniments, a copy of your communication
                                to Mr. Drouyn de Lhuys, and of his reply thereto, relative to the
                                authenticity of the published letter of Marshal Bazaine to the
                                republican general in Mexico, has been received.</p>
                            <p>Your inquiry seems to have been discreet, and it is approved.</p>
                            <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>